text: The canton of Marignane is an administrative division of the Bouches-du-Rhône department, in southeastern France. At the French canton reorganisation which came into effect in March 2015, it was expanded from 2 to 7 communes. Its seat is in Marignane.Décret n° 2014-271 du 27 février 2014 portant délimitation des cantons dans le département des Bouches-du-Rhône It consists of the following communes: #Carry-le-Rouet #Châteauneuf-les-Martigues #Ensuès-la-Redonne #Gignac-la-Nerthe #Marignane #Le Rove #Sausset-les-Pins ==References== Category:Cantons of Bouches-du-Rhône
